attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered ransomware. Other contributing factors were that it has known exploits and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated Windows backdoor or information stealer with screen-scraping and C2 capabilities. Key behaviors include: 1. Extensive dynamic API resolving (sub_40182a) using custom wrappers for LoadLibraryA and GetProcAddress to evade static analysis. 2. Spyware functionality in sub_404255, which captures screen data, constructs BMP files (header 0x4D42), and potentially saves them to disk or registry keys. 3. Command and Control (C2) communication in sub_4031ee via HTTP POST requests using a Base64 alphabet for data encoding and format strings (%.8x=%s) for exfiltration. 4. Recursive file system enumeration (sub_4067ad) and persistence mechanisms via registry manipulation (sub_404037). 5. Anti-analysis features including OS version checking (sub_401f0f) and dynamic heap management.
